8. Atilius. This was Atilius Crescens, an intimate friend of Pliny. Cf. ii. 14, 6 for another saying of his. From vi. 8, where Pliny writes in the interest of Atilius, we learn that they were intimate from boyhood ; that Atilius was an ardent student, but of limited means. Pliny also speaks of his facetiae (nosti facetias hominis).
